{
  "stem": "22237.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they were throwing stones through all the windows-- bricks and all kinds of things through those windows.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I realized that they're breaking all the windows of the Jews, and that is what became the infamous Kristallnacht, crystal night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The first thing, I was hiding under the bed, and I realized I have to make my own decisions now.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I have nobody anymore to tell me what to do next.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was always my parents who told us what to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I decided-- I looked again through the window, and I decided that they're going to come through this window, also.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So I put on-- I dressed myself warm, and I ran out of the house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I was afraid-- I was always afraid to stay in the house since I was deported.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I ran out of the house, and I ran down.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I ran to the next block, and there was the-- some place nearby was this synagogue-- Breuer Synagogue, spelled B-R-E-U-E-R.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And that synagogue was in flames, and there were young people standing there throwing stones through these beautiful windows.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It was a gorgeous synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It was-- it was well known, beautiful, and it was up in flames.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And I was standing there at the corner in awe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The synagogue was something-- we went to the synagogue even the recent Friday, the recent Sabbath, and now the synagogue is in flames.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I couldn't get over that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But I realized very quickly that I can't push my luck, and I kept on running.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "I thought-- this was just taking place in our street.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And I just kept on running and running any place, just to get away from this chaos.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And then I realized that they were still throwing bricks in many other windows.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
